{{Accessory | Name=N64 Transfer Pak | Guid=3000-59 | Deck=The Transfer Pak was an accessory for the Nintendo 64 that allowed the transfer of data between specific Nintendo 64 games and their counterparts on the Game Boy. | Image=https://www.giantbomb.com/a/uploads/scale_super/16/164924/2505619-transferpak.jpg}}
<div id='imageData' data-json='{"infobox":{"file":"2505619-transferpak.jpg","path":"16\/164924\/","mime":"image\/jpeg","sizes":"square_small,scale_small,square_tiny,square_medium,square_mini,scale_tiny,square_avatar,scale_medium,screen_medium,scale_large,scale_avatar,ignore_jpg_scale_small,scale_super,screen_kubrick","caption":""},"background":[]}' />
Unlike the [[Concepts/Super_Game_Boy_Enhancement|Super Game Boy]], the Transfer Pak (with few exceptions) did not allow play of [[Platforms/Game_Boy|Game Boy]] games on the television. Instead, its primary purpose was to transfer or unlock data between two versions/counterparts of a game.
