{{Accessory | Name=OSVR Hacker Development Kit | Guid=3000-96 | Deck=Open Source Virtual Reality Headmounted Display | Image=https://www.giantbomb.com/a/uploads/scale_super/30/308862/2829359-osvr-hdk-gallery-01-v2__store_gallery.png}}
<div id='imageData' data-json='{"infobox":{"file":"2829359-osvr-hdk-gallery-01-v2__store_gallery.png","path":"30\/308862\/","mime":"image\/png","sizes":"square_tiny,square_medium,square_small,scale_super,square_mini,scale_small,square_avatar,scale_avatar,screen_medium,scale_large,scale_medium,screen_kubrick,scale_tiny","caption":null},"background":[]}' />
==Overview== Open Source Virtual Reality (OSVR) is a virtual reality head-up display project that is an open hardware device and uses open source software. OSVR consists of two main and independent parts: open source schematics and drawings and open source software. Open source software enables VR developers to discover, configure, and control VR devices across a wide range of operating systems. This software is licensed under Apache 2.0. The main sponsors of the project are [https:/www.razer.com Razer Inc.] and Sensics. The HDK1 Self-Build Kit, version 1.4, was available to order in 2017 from the developer and enthusiast on the [https://www2.razer.com/vr/hdk1 project website].
